The paper discusses the use of knowledge graph embeddings for machine learning tasks, which falls under the scope of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on the reproducibility and transferability of the proposed models, which is relevant to the database (cs.DB) and natural language processing (cs.CL) communities. Additionally, the paper mentions downstream tasks such as question answering and fact-checking, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
